This suggests that `(μ + ν).ang = μ.ang + ν.ang`.

If this is true, then we can prove the linearity of the integral:
`∫ x, (μ + ν).ang x • f x ∂((μ + ν).var) = ∫ x, (μ.ang x + ν.ang x) • f x ∂(μ.var + ν.var)`
`= ∫ x, (μ.ang x • f x) d(μ.var + ν.var) + ∫ x, (ν.ang x • f x) d(μ.var + ν.var)`
`= ∫ x, μ.ang x • f x dμ.var + ∫ x, ν.ang x • f x dν.var`
`= ∫ x, μ.ang x • f x ∂μ.var + ∫ x, ν.ang x • f x ∂ν.var`
`= ∫ f dμ + ∫ f dν`

So, to complete the proof, we need to establish that `(μ + ν).ang = μ.ang + ν.ang`.

Let's try to prove this formally in Lean:

```tactics
